parameters:
The spirit of the shrine maiden: "...What business do the people of Kusechi
have with us?"

The chieftain: "We have come to receive the curse of destruction from our
ancestors."

The spirit of the shrine maiden: "...How convenient for you... Not
satisfied with merely toying with our bodies, now you seek to exploit our
souls as well..."

The chieftain: "I am fully aware of the great sacrifices made by our
predecessors, allowing us to live. However, there is something we must
protect at all costs..."
The spirit of the shrine maiden: "Oh?"

The chieftain: "I do not care if this body perishes. Please, bestow upon me
your power!"

The spirit of the shrine maiden: "...Stop it... Even if you bow your head
like that, our feelings will not be cleared."

The spirit of the shrine maiden: "Alright, alright... It's not like no one
is willing to do it. Just that..."

The spirit of the shrine maiden: "To obtain that technique, you must defeat
this one..."
Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "This burden is too heavy for you... so give up..."
Chieftain: "...Understood. So I just need to defeat this creature, right?"
Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Hah... Don't blame me for what happens..."
Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Hah... That's why I warned you..."

Chieftain: "...I've caused... you both... suffering... This was... my
attempt at... atonement..."

Chieftain: "But... it seems... I wasn't... lenient enough... Age... has...
defeated me..."
Chieftain: "It's no use... I'm done for..."

Chieftain: "I couldn't do anything for you... I'm truly... sorry...
Please..."
Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Stop this! These ones are different!"
Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "No! You mustn't defeat that demon!"
Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Fool! If you defeat him..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Sigh... The Curse of Ruin... It's a forbidden art
passed down among the people of Kuseshi..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Indeed... It's a technique that erases the
existence of the target in exchange for the life of the user..."
Umi: "It's okay... I came prepared for this..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Ho... So you are the current shrine maiden... You
seem to have hardly any cursed energy accumulated... If it stays like this,
Lord Kuseshirei's power will run wild..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "That's right... By offering cursed energy as a
tribute, the people of Kuseshi have been able to suppress Lord Kuseshirei's
power. In exchange for the corruption of the shrine maiden's soul..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Exactly... By harboring negative emotions within
the shrine maiden, they heightened the cursed energy and offered that power
to appease Lord Kuseshirei's wrath."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "In my time, it was even worse... I was violated by
all the men in the village, one after another, in front of my beloved
husband..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "But as time passed, that custom gradually fell out
of practice... There were many like that chieftain who tried to save the
young from old traditions..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "As a result... Lord Kuseshirei's seal has begun to
loosen."
Kru: "What happens if the seal loosens?"

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "It could be the end of this world. Lord Kuseshirei
will indiscriminately impregnate life, and eventually, all life will be
replaced."

Kru: "I'm okay... It's nothing... It's just that I've heard this story
before..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "We have risked our lives to suppress Lord
Kuseshirei... But being bound here like this feels so futile."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "Now, girl... You possess the forbidden art, but do
not use that power recklessly..."

Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "I am tired... I have spoken too much after such a
long time... And..."
Shrine Maiden's Ghost: "...You two are too dazzling for me..."
